@node xcmar93 " XCopy March 93 "

XCopy March 93

BUG FIXES
---------
- The XCopy Display got currupted, when the Workbench ScreenMode was
  DlbNTSC/PAL or similar. Fixed.
- FORMAT asked for a diskname, although track 40 was not selected and
  wouldn't get formatted anyway.
- The Directory routine did't close it's window, when an error occured
  during reading.
- X-Copy sometimes detected a non-virus bootblock as an AIDS virus.

UPDATES
-------
- XCopy comes with the Bootblock.library by Safe Hex International.
  This library contains checks for about 150 viruses and will be
  be used for virus-detection, if present.
- Clicking on the ASI Logo in the upper left rectangle of the screen
  will display the version of the Bootblock.library. If the library
  or it's brainfile couldn't be loaded, there will be an error message
  displayed instead.
- The functions INSTALL, FORMAT and QFORMAT are now able to create
  FFS and OFS bootable or non-bootable disks.
- Most of the Functions are now accessible from the Keyboard:
    D = Select DOSCOPY       O = Select OPTIMIZE
    P = Select DOSCOPY+      P = Select FORMAT
    B = Select BAMCOPY       B = Select QFORMAT
    N = Select NIBBLE        I = Select INSTALL
                             S = Select SPEEDCHK
    V = Toggle Verify for all Target Drives
    F1 = Start (or RETURN)   F4 = Disk Info
    F2 = Repeat (or R)       F5 = Directory
    F3 = Stop (or ESC)       F6 = Default
    F10 = Exit
@endnode


